#: ../../F/furrfu.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet; written, only rarely spoken] Written-only equivalent of \"Sheesh! "
"\"; it is, in fact, \"sheesh\" modified by :ref:`rot13`\\. Evolved in "
"mid-1992 as a response to notably silly postings repeating urban myths on "
"the Usenet newsgroup :samp:`alt.folklore.urban`\\, after some posters "
"complained that \"Sheesh!\" as a response to :ref:`newbie`\\s was being "
"overused. See also :ref:`FOAF`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet。書き言葉で、ごくまれにしか話されない]「Sheesh!(やれやれ!)」の書き言葉専用の等価物。実のところ、これは「sheesh」を\\ "
":ref:`rot13`\\ で変換したものだ。1992年半ばに、Usenetのニュースグループ\\ "
":samp:`alt.folklore.urban`\\ で、都市伝説を繰り返す著しくばかげた投稿への応答として生まれた。\\ "
":ref:`newbie`\\ への応答として「Sheesh!」が使われすぎていると一部の投稿者が不満を述べた後のことだ。\\ "
":ref:`FOAF`\\ も参照。"
